<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kuchma Suggests Kravchuk `Might Become the Winner' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kuchma Suggests Kravchuk `Might Become the Winner' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2206072594 Lvov POST-INFORM in Ukrainian 1200 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2206072594 </F>
<F P=104>  Lvov POST-INFORM </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 16 June, Leonid Kuchma, one of the candidates 
for Ukraine's president, visited Kharkov. At the news 
conference he pointed out that the Interregional Bloc of Reforms 
had been a declaratory structure and attempts had failed to form 
a party on its basis. 
  Speaking about the election of Vitaliy Masol to the post of 
Ukraine's prime minister, Kuchma voiced his discontent, saying 
that "in economic terms this was a step back." 
  Leonid Kuchma stated that he was not sure whether he would 
be 
able to win the elections and suggested that Leonid Kravchuk 
might become the winner. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

