<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk's Economic Adviser Urges Increased Pace of Reform </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kravchuk's Economic Adviser Urges Increased Pace of Reform </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2206115094 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 1000 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2206115094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign investors will only begin to deposit their 
capital in the Ukrainian economy if there is political and 
economic stabilization. This was stated in an interview with 
the UKRAINSKIYE VEDOMOSTI magazine by Bohdan Havrylyshyn, an 
independent adviser to the Ukrainian president. He noted that 
if the current pace of reform is maintained, Ukraine may end up 
in international isolation and be transformed into an economic 
refugee. Bohdan Havrylyshyn emphasized that without conducting 
deep economic transformations, Ukraine cannot count on financial 
assistance from the West. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

