<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Association Asks Presidential Candidates To Withdraw </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Association Asks Presidential Candidates To Withdraw </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2106211994 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1925 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2106211994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev [no dateline as received]--The press service of 
the Ukraina democratic association reports that the association 
has written to presidential candidates Valeriy Babych and Petro 
Talanchuk, urging them to withdraw from the presidential race 
for the benefit of Leonid Kravchuk. The statement points out 
that, "in view of the threat to our state's independence, the 
Ukraina democratic association has resolved that the 
situation can be improved only if the current president, Leonid 
Kravchuk, who has proved himself to be a consistent champion of 
Ukrainian statehood and the country's democratic development, 
wins the 26 June election." 
  The Ukraina democratic association has prepared documents in 
support of Kravchuk, signed by the leaders of most of the 
association's parties and organizations. Support groups 
campaigning for the current president will soon leave for 
Ukraine's eastern and southern regions. 
  The press service of the Ukraina democratic association told 
UNIAN that the appeal to the presidential candidates was sent on 
15 June, but no reply has been received thus far. 

</TEXT>

