<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister meets TU Leader, Discuss Tariff Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prime Minister meets TU Leader, Discuss Tariff Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2106162494 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 2115 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2106162494 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev, 20 Jun -- As Ukrainian TV has reported, newly 
elected Prime Minister Vitaliy Masol met Oleksandr Stoyan, 
chairman of the Ukraine's Federation of Trade Unions, and other 
trade union leaders. They discussed the need to adopt urgent 
measures in order to increase production, which would remove 
tension in most of the sectors of the national economy, and 
promote a strengthening of workers' social protection. 
  They also discussed problems of social insurance and ways of 
resolving conflicts between the government and trade union 
concerning the implementation and setting up of a tariff 
agreement. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

