<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Increased Crime Result of Worsening Economic Situation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2106110394 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Kazakh 0100 GMT 
21 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2106110394 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty Kazakh Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Kazakh </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Summary from poor reception] The law-enforcement bodies of 
North Kazakhstan Oblast report that due to the worsening 
economic situation there was a increase by a factor of 2.5 in 
the number of crimes in the first quarter of 1994 compared to 
the same period in 1993. Of 1,950 crimes in this period, 380 
were committed by young people in their twenties and 321 crimes 
were committed by unemployed people. 

