<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Border Guards Fight Continued Provocations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Border Guards Fight Continued Provocations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2206095994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0822 
GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2206095994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Vadim Byrkin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 22 Jun -- Having the tendency to further 
aggravation was the description of the situation on the 
Tajik-Afghan frontier given at the press bureau of the Russian 
border guards where the ITAR-TASS correspondent inquired today. 
  According to the border guards' reports, the movement of 
groups of fighters from the provinces of Konduz and Takhor in 
Afghanistan toward Badakhshan continues, for the purpose of 
further dispatch to the territory of Tajikistan. By 22 June the 
number of fighters has reached some 900 men. 
  The personnel of the Pyanj, Moscow, and Khorog frontier 
detachments have since 18 June, in five instances prevented 
illegal crossings of armed gangs of Tajikistan's Islamic Revival 
Movement into the territory of the Republic. Leaders of the 
irreconcilable Tajik opposition and field commanders have been 
given instructions to mount a series of armed and diversionary 
operations against the subunits of the Pyanj and Moscow frontier 
detachments, and also against the civilian population of the 
frontier regions of Tajikistan. 
  At the press bureau of the Russian border guards it was 
reported that on the territory of Gorno-Badakhshan Autonomous 
Oblast, in the past few days narcotics traders have twice 
attempted to blockade the frontier detachment's base so as to 
provoke the Russian border guards into taking counter measures. 
  The border guards are taking the necessary measures to 
prevent any provocations or cases of frontier violations and are 
prepared to act with utmost decisiveness. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

