<H3> <TI>   Disagreement Centers on Defense Spending </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Disagreement Centers on Defense Spending </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2206124894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1235 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2206124894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Pavel Kuznetsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 22 TASS -- The State Duma (lower 
chamber) of the Russian Parliament lacked five votes on 
Wednesday to approve the federal draft budget under the third 
reading, but will reconsider it in the evening. 
  With only 221 votes for it, the draft, which was amended 
after its second reading a few days ago, failed to overcome the 
226-vote hurdle. 
  The major disagreement is the defence spendings. The Duma 
wants to keep them at the 40-trillion rouble level, while the 
upper chamber, the Federation Council, wants to increase the 
appropriations to 55 trillion. 

</TEXT>

