<H3> <TI>   Duma Rejects Communist Attack on NATO Partnership </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Duma Rejects Communist Attack on NATO Partnership </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2206081594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0808 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2206081594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS parliamentary correspondent Ivan Novikov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 22 TASS -- The Russian State Duma 
rejected on Wednesday a communist proposal to "declare null and 
void" the upcoming Russia's joining the NATO "Partnership for 
Peace" plan which is to be signed by Foreign Minister Andrey 
Kozyrev in Brussels today. 
  Communist leader Gennadiy Zyuganov said in the lower house 
that the NATO partnership plan is "US expansionism aimed against 
Russia". 
  He compared it to the notorious "Barbarossa" plan of Adolf 
Hitler which was used to invade the former Soviet Union exactly 
53 years ago - on June 22, 1941 when Nazi Germany attacked the 
USSR. 
  However, the Duma voted down the communist proposal to 
include the issue into the agenda. 

</TEXT>

