<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rybkin Favors Extending Term of Deputies </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rybkin Favors Extending Term of Deputies </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2106174494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1542 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2106174494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Speaker of the State Duma (the lower house of 
Russian parliament) Ivan Rybkin has expressed support to his 
counterpart from the upper house Vladimir Shumeyko's proposal to 
extend the term in office of deputies and the president. 
  In an interview with Interfax, he said the idea was first 
put 
forward by member of the State Duma Mikhail Poltoranin two 
months ago. 
  However, Rybkin thinks three main conditions must be met 
before the proposal is implemented: the economy must show signs 
of stabilization in the next two or three months; the country's 
legislative network be arranged in a proper way; and the two 
houses prove workable. 
  Rybkin said he would be happy to see the terms of office for 
the parliament and head of state extended after those conditions 
had been met. 

</TEXT>

