<H3> <TI>   Nakhichevan Parliament Speaker Visits Iran </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nakhichevan Parliament Speaker Visits Iran </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2106130194 Baku TURAN in English 0735 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2106130194 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baku, June 20 (TURAN)--The head of Nakhichevan 
Autonomous Republic [NAR] Supreme Mejlis Namik Gasanov was in 
Iran from June 15 until June 18 with an official visit, told 
TURAN the chief of parliament press-service Ali Gasanov. 
  During the visit Gasanov met with Ali Abdol-Alizade, 
ostandar 
(head) of province Eastern Azerbaijan. An agreement on cargo 
transportation from Baku to Nakhichevan through Iran and from 
Turkey to Azerbaijan through Iran was reached. 
  Gasanov and Abdol-Alizade signed an executive agreement 
between province Eastern Azerbaijan (Iran) and NAR. According 
to the agreement goods totalling 8.8 million US dollars, 20,000 
tons of grain, 15,000 tons of kerosene, 20,000 tons of mazut, 
10,000 tons of diesel fuel, 5,000 tons of coal, 3,000 tons of 
sugar and 1200 tons of liquefied gas will be delivered to 
Nakhichevan from East Azerbaijan. 
  Gurbanali Saadat, ostandar of Western Azerbaijan province 
met 
with Namik Gasanov in Urmie on June 17. The sides discussed the 
issues of board trade, of cultural and humanitarian cooperation. 
An agreement on trade and economic cooperation was signed on 
June 18. According to agreement, fuel and products totalling 3.5 
million dollars will be delivered to Nakhichevan from West 
Azerbaijan within 6 months. 
  During the visit Namik Gasanov met also with business 
circles 
of Iran, visited tractor plant and enterprise dealing with fruit 
juice production. 

</TEXT>

