<H3> <TI>   Russian Generals Arrive To Coordinate Peacekeeping </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Generals Arrive To Coordinate Peacekeeping </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2106164294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1319 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2106164294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On Tuesday coordinators of the peace-keeping 
operation in the Georgian-Abkhaz conflict zone Russian generals 
Aleksandr Sokolov, Valeriy Kuznetsov and Vasiliy Yakushev 
arrived in Zugdidi (West Georgia). This was reported to 
Interfax at the press center of the Georgian Interior Ministry 
force. The generals met the commander of the force Vladimir 
Chikovani and the local administration and discussed the details 
of the coming operation. 
  Also on Tuesday the Council of the Federation, the upper 
house of the Russian parliament, approved the sending of Russian 
peace-keepers to the conflict zone. 
  According to well-informed sources in Tbilisi, the 
restoration of the bridge across the Inguri river has not yet 
started. Russian troops on both sides are building temporary 
premises for future checkpoints. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

