<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shevardnadze on Russian Role </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shevardnadze on Russian Role </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2106203594 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network in Georgian 1800 
GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2106203594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network </F>
<F P=105>  Georgian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today Eduard Shevardnadze, the Georgian head of 
state and chairman of parliament, received Russian Ambassador to 
Georgia Vladimir Zemskiy. The ambassador presented to the head 
of state a letter from Boris Yeltsin in which the Russian 
president thanks Eduard Shevardnadze for his message of 
greetings on Russian Independence Day, and expresses confidence 
that friendship and cooperation between Russia and Georgia will 
continue for the benefit of the two countries' peoples. 
  The two discussed today's decision by Russia's Federation 
Council, authorizing the deployment of Russian peacekeeping 
forces in the conflict zone in Abkhazia. The head of state said 
that the decision is very important. He stressed that this 
international initiative by Russia is of historic importance not 
only for Georgia, and that its success would be a prerequisite 
for stability in the Transcaucasus. In the opinion of Eduard 
Shevardnadze, the success of the operation will boost Russia's 
international reputation, and would be a positive example to 
other countries. 

</TEXT>

