<H3> <TI>   Kitovani Suggests Georgian Peacekeeping Force </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kitovani Suggests Georgian Peacekeeping Force </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2206112194 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 21 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM2206112194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Vitaliy Denisov under the "KRASNAYA ZVEZDA and </F>
News Agency Correspondents Report" rubric: "Will `Blue Helmets' 
Suit the National Guard?"] 
  [Text] Tbilisi -- "All states belonging to the CIS must 
have peacemaking battalions, since we cannot rely on Russia all 
the time," Georgian parliamentary deputy Tengiz Kitovani 
believes. 
  He has advocated the creation of the republic's own 
peacemaking units, so as to have the possibility of 
participating in the settlement of conflicts in neighboring 
regions. He proposes to form battalions of "blue helmets" on 
the basis of the National Guard and the recently disbanded 
military police. At the same time Kitovani ignored the question 
of where it is proposed to find the funds to maintain them. 

</TEXT>

