<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Troops Clear Mines Near Inguri River Bridge </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Troops Clear Mines Near Inguri River Bridge </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2206120494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1005 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2206120494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russian troops finished the removal of mines from 
the region adjacent to the village of Rukhi near the bridge 
across the River Inguri, the press center of the Russian troops 
in the Transcaucasus told Interfax. Control posts are being 
built on both banks of the river, after which the work to 
restore the Inguri bridge will begin. 
  Deputy Commander of the Russian troops in the Transcaucasus 
Major-General Vassiliy Belchenko told Interfax that two 
battalions were ready to take part in the peacekeeping mission 
in Abkhazia. He said that these battalions' bases will be 
determined by Deputy Defense Minister Georgiy Kondratyev who is 
in charge of the peacekeeping operation. The operation itself 
is to begin during the next two days, said Belchenko. 
  The Georgian Defense Ministry's press center informed 
Interfax that the Georgian troops and heavy equipment had been 
removed from the security zone in the region of the peacekeeping 
operation over to the Senaki Region. Only local police units 
still remain in the 12-kilometer zone in the Zugdidi and the 
Tsalendzhikha regions, said the Georgian Defense Ministry's 
spokesman. 

</TEXT>

