<F P=105>  Georgian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tbilisi, 21 Jun--Eduard Shevardnadze, chairman of 
the Georgian parliament and head of state, announced at today's 
session of parliament that he had a telephone conversation with 
Russian Federation Defense Minister Pavel Grachev. The 
conversation was held at the initiative of the Russian defense 
minister. 
  Grachev informed Shevardnadze that Russia's Federation 
Council met today. The Council examined the Russian president's 
decree authorizing the deployment of peacekeeping troops in 
Abkhazia. Grachev said that the two-hour meeting had been tense, 
with a great number of questions having been asked. There was a 
vote, during which President Yeltsin's decree was approved by an 
absolute majority of votes. Therefore, the introduction of 
Russian Federation peacekeeping troops to the region of Abkhazia 
will begin 22 June. 

