BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "The Registration of Refugees Has Not </F>
Ended"] 
  [Text] The IBERIA news agency has been informed by the 
Committee for Refugees and Forcibly Displaced Persons that there 
are currently about 295,000 refugees in the Republic of Georgia 
of which 60,000 are in Tbilisi. They receive monthly assistance 
amounting to 70,000 coupons [per person]. This amount increases 
according to inflation. As regards humanitarian aid, this is 
distributed directly in the rayons according to local 
registration. 
  Preparations are being made to register anew refugees and 
forcibly displaced persons; this should take place on 18-19 
June. Refugees are to be given new identification cards, which 
have already been printed and sent to the rayons. 

</TEXT>

