Secretariat: "For Mutually Advantageous Cooperation"] 
  [Text] On 15 June, a protocol was signed in the 
"Mtatsminda" business club between the International Fund for 
Reconstruction and Development and the Georgian Citizens' Fund. 
  The main aim of the agreement is to promote wide-scale 
economic reforms in Georgia and lay the ground for the 
development of business contacts between entrepreneurs in 
conditions of mutually advantageous cooperation. Particular 
attention is devoted in the document to guaranteeing the 
protection of the rights of the private entrepreneur. 
  The protocol was signed on behalf of the International Fund 
for Reconstruction and Development by its vice president Sergey 
Shurygin, and on behalf of the Georgian Citizens Fund by its 
president Gogi Kavtaradze. 

