BFN 

  [Excerpt] [Passage omitted] The Estonian authorities 
learned of today's edict by Boris Yeltsin from the mass media. 
Raul Malk, vice chancellor of the Estonian Foreign Ministry, 
told our radio station that the text of the decree had not been 
conveyed to Tallinn by diplomatic channels. 
  [Begin Malk recording] The implementation of the 
presidential 
edict would signify, in present conditions, that one state 
thinks up some line, and without agreement with the other side 
declares it as the state border of the two states. The state 
border cannot be established unless its line is agreed with the 
other side. Today's decree on a unilateral act in matters of 
the state frontier with Estonia gives the impression that when 
all is said and done, such is Russia's interest in the 
normalization of relations with Estonia overall. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

