<H3> <TI>   Saeima Passes Law on Citizenship </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Saeima Passes Law on Citizenship </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2106183794 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1700 GMT 21 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2106183794 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>
<F P=105>  Latvian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] The citizenship bill was debated in the Latvian 
Saeima today on its third reading. As expected, the debate was 
primarily devoted to Clause 14, which regulates the general 
arrangements for the naturalization of non-citizens. [passage 
omitted] 
  The quota principle could be an obstacle to admission to the 
Council of Europe. This was pointed out in a speech by Prime 
Minister Valdis Birkavs. In a secret ballot, this quota was 
removed from the law by majority vote. Thereby, the Saeima this 
evening accepted the law on citizenship. The voting in the 
secret ballot was: 66 deputies for; 11 against; three 
abstentions. 

</TEXT>

