<H3> <TI>   First Large Enterprises Registered Insolvent </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    First Large Enterprises Registered Insolvent </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2206095294 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0900 GMT 
22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2206095294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The first large Russian industrial enterprises have 
been entered on the state register of insolvency. The list of 
enterprises was drawn up by the Russian Committee on 
Machine-Building. About 40 plants were registered. These 
crisis-ridden plants are unable to pay taxes, settle up with 
suppliers of raw materials, or pay wages. These enterprises 
will now have to change the way they run their business or else 
acknowledge their insolvency and go into voluntary 
self-liquidation. 

</TEXT>

