<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bank `Experiment' Averts Miners' Strike </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bank `Experiment' Averts Miners' Strike </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2106123194 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 21 Jun 94 
First Edition p 2 </F>

<F P=103> PM2106123194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Successful Experiment"] </F>
  [Text] To all appearances the country is no longer 
threatened by miners' strikes caused by the nonpayments crisis. 
The specialists from the Russian Coal and Raw Material Mutual 
[sovmestnyy] Bank have found a way out of the apparent deadlock. 
  The first "industrial experiment" has already shown the high 
degree of effectiveness of the decisions which have been found. 
A financial chain linked the "Vorkutaugol" association, the 
Novyy Lipetsk metallurgical combine, the Vyksa pipe welders, 
and the transport workers and oil extraction workers. A 
clearing accounts procedure has been developed for each 
enterprise. 
  Nonetheless it is still too early to rejoice. The country is 
in acute need of modern financial legislation. 
  A realistic way out of the situation is the creation of 
financial and industrial groups. In the coal industry this 
process has already begun. In the opinion of specialists, the 
profitability of "buying and selling" operations is receding 
into the past. Life has shown that the future of the economy 
and its normalization belong to the producers. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

