<H3> <TI>   Widespread Tax Evasion Cuts Revenues by 10 Percent </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Widespread Tax Evasion Cuts Revenues by 10 Percent </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2106151994 Moscow SELSKAYA ZHIZN in Russian 21 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM2106151994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow SELSKAYA ZHIZN </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Taxes: Game of Hide and Seek"] </F>
  [Text] There has been a tax collection shortfall of around 
10 percent this year. The lower chamber of parliament was 
informed of this by Vladimir Gusev, leader of the State Taxation 
Service. The basic reason for this, according to him, is the 
nonpayments crisis and numerous cases of tax evasion. 
  Briefing deputies on progress in fulfilling the Russian 
President's Edict "On the Implementation of a Tax Amnesty in 
1993," Vladimir Gusev noted that nonpayment of taxes has 
essentially become widespread. He cited the following figures: 
Since the presidential edict came into force 44,000 corporate 
bodies and 2,000 individuals guilty of ignoring tax legislation 
have been detected. As a result the exchequer has experienced a 
shortfall of 350 billion rubles. 

</TEXT>

