<H3> <TI>   Population Declines by 1 Million </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Population Declines by 1 Million </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK2106111094 Moscow MOSKOVSKAYA PRAVDA in Russian 21 Jun 94 
p 1 </F>

<F P=103> MK2106111094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow MOSKOVSKAYA PRAVDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report under the "What's the News" rubric: </F>
"Russian Population Down by One Million"] 
  [Text] The Russian president's Commission on the Affairs 
of Women, Family, and Demography has held a meeting. Commission 
Chairman Yekaterina Lyakhova delivered a report "On the Status 
of Families in the Russian Federation." 
  The report noted, in particular, that as of 1 January 1994 
Russia had a population of 148.4 million people, that is, the 
Russian population has declined by nearly 1 million from 1992. 
Mortality has exceeded birth rate. 
  The author attributed this to the worsening of Russian 
families' social situation. For instance, the new system of 
child benefits introduced in January 1994 does not ensure even a 
level of benefits comparable with that of January 1991. 

</TEXT>

