<F P=102>   LD2106162894 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0859 
GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2106162894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 21 Jun -- On Monday Boris Yeltsin approved 
the statute of a commission for higher military posts, higher 
military ranks, and higher special ranks of the council for 
cadre policy under the Russian president. 
  The commission's task is to examine the representations by 
heads of federal bodies of executive authority of the Russian 
president on appointing servicemen to top military posts and on 
relieving them of these posts in the Defense Ministry, the 
Interior Ministry, bodies and troops of the federal agency of 
government communications and information, counterintelligence 
bodies, the main directorate for protection, the security 
service of the Russian president, the foreign intelligence 
service, and other formations. 

</TEXT>

