<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Observes Nuclear Forces' Vigil Procedures </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Observes Nuclear Forces' Vigil Procedures </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2206102194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1009 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2206102194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 22 TASS -- The press service of the 
Russian presudent circulated the following announcement in 
Wednesday: 
  "The president of the Russian Federation, the President of 
the United States amnd the prime minister of the United Kingdom 
are known to have agreed, with a view to enhancing 
confidence-building measures and reducing nuclear confrontation, 
that from May 30, this year, the strategic nuclear forces of the 
three states are no longer targeted on one another and keep 
operational vigil with zero flight settings. 
  "Today, on June 22, President Boris Yeltsin as the supreme 
commander-in-chief visited the command centre of the Armed 
Forces of the Russian Federation. 
  "Defence Minister P.S. Grachev and Chief of the General 
Staff M.P. Kolesnikov demonstrated to Yeltsin the combat vigil 
arrangements and the procedure for the control of the country's 
nuclear forces in realisation of the agreement between Russia, 
the U.S. and Britain. 
  "The Russian Federation has fully met its commitments. Its 
strategic nuclear forces keep combat vigil in line with new 
political realities that have arisen since the end of the cold 
war." 

</TEXT>

