<F P=101> Military, Nuclear &amp; Space Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Budget Amendment Concerns Nuclear Safety Committee </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Budget Amendment Concerns Nuclear Safety Committee </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2106105494 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1000 GMT 
21 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2106105494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The press office of Gosatomnadzor [the State 
Committee for Supervision of Nuclear and Radiation Safety] 
reports that Amendment 185, which envisages the allocation of 
560 billion rubles for ensuring nuclear and radiation safety at 
atomic power stations, is missing from the final version of the 
federal budget for reasons that have not been established. 
Moreover, the Ministry of Atomic Energy pledged to return this 
money as soon as it was paid by consumers for electricity 
produced by atomic power stations. The amendment was backed by 
the State Duma's power-engineering and ecology committees and 
was included in the draft budget passed at a second reading. 
However, the amendment is not in the final version of the 
budget that is due to be approved on 22 June. Atomic energy 
industry workers are sounding the alarm, claiming that to shut 
down all atomic power stations would require significantly more 
funds to ensure minimum safety standards. 

</TEXT>

