<F P=101> Military, Nuclear &amp; Space Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cosmonauts Continue Mir Mission </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cosmonauts Continue Mir Mission </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2106115194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1121 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2106115194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mission Control Centre June 21 TASS -- The Russian 
scientific research space complex "Mir" continues its flight 
with the 15th main space expedition members on board. 
  On Tuesday the crew spent a major part of its working time 
on 
preventive measures of the space station's temperature control 
systems, the mission control centre informed ITAR-TASS today. 
  During the day the cosmonauts will prepare for their 
forthcoming experiments with the "Trek" apparatus, which is 
meant for research of streams of superheavy nuclei of space 
rays, and the "Kaf-1000" camera. There are also plans to 
conduct medical checkup of the cosmonauts. 
  According to telemtric data and crew reports, onboard 
systems 
of the orbital complex are functioning normally. The health of 
cosmonauts Viktor Afanasyev, Yuriy Usachev and Valeriy Polyakov 
is good. 

</TEXT>

