<H3> <TI>   Kebich Discusses Cooperation With Austrian Chancellor </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kebich Discusses Cooperation With Austrian Chancellor </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2106142094 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1600 
GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2106142094 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>
<F P=105>  Belarusian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Austrian Chancellor Franz Vranitzky and Prime 
Minister Vyacheslaw Kebich held negotiations in Vienna today. 
Local political observers deemed the recently established 
contacts between the two countries' leaders as fruitful. 
Austria supports the balanced political line of Belarus and its 
moving toward achieving accord within the CIS, as well as 
strengthening ties with both Russia and European states. During 
the negotiations, emphasis was placed on ways of seeking new 
forms of mutual cooperation; interest was also expressed in 
expanding contacts in the areas of politics, economics, and 
culture, according to an ITAR-TASS correspondent. 

</TEXT>

