<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Said To Reach Agreement on Oil Credit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Said To Reach Agreement on Oil Credit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2206094394 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1600 
GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2206094394 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>
<F P=105>  Belarusian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] As has already been reported, Belarusian Prime 
Minister Vyachaslaw Kebich is on a short working visit to 
Austria. The intention of the visit is to sign a document 
securing a $100 million credit to our Republic from the Austrian 
Government. Those credits will be used to purchase Russian oil 
to meet Belarusian needs and fund its subsequent processing at 
the Novopolotsk Oil Refinery. It is planned that a [word 
indistinct] portion of the gasoline and other oil products will 
be sold on European markets, which will provide hard currency to 
repay the credit. Vyachaslaw Kebich held a prolonged meeting 
with Austrian Chancellor Franz Vranitzky. Also discussed at the 
negotiations was the issue of Belarus joining the GATT. 
Agreement was reached on all issues. 

</TEXT>

