<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Defends Record, Policy in Pre-Election Statement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Defends Record, Policy in Pre-Election Statement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2206103194 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 0700 
GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2206103194 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>
<F P=105>  Belarusian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In accordance with the Constitution, the elections 
of the first Belarusian president will take place tomorrow. In 
this connection, the Cabinet of Ministers has issued a statement. 
  The popularly elected president should become a guarantor of 
the sovereignty, national security, and territorial integrity of 
our state, as well as ensure political and economic stability, 
peace, and accord within society, and implement urgent tasks 
related to foreign policy and foreign trade. In the process of 
preparations for the elections, especially during its final 
stages, some candidates for the highest state position have made 
the government the prime target of their criticism, mounting the 
most incredible charges against it. It is being drilled into 
the people that the government has no course of action to 
resolve many complex economic problems. Subject to attacks, the 
statement reads, are even attempts by the Cabinet of Ministers 
to support state-run industrial and agricultural enterprises, as 
well as measures intended to reduce price increases, 
unemployment, and social deregulation of the market. The 
government, the statement stresses, considers it a task of 
national importance to restore the Republic's economic potential 
and ensure its integration into the international system of 
economic and political relations. Its integration policies have 
been accepted by the international community. Their most 
important element is economic union with Russia. The concluded 
agreements have already produced concrete results. As never 
before, the Republic needs mutual support, understanding, and a 
uniting of the efforts of all people to overcome the difficult 
situation. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

