<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Number of Native Military Officers Increases `Noticeably' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Number of Native Military Officers Increases `Noticeably' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2106134794 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1600 
GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2106134794 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>
<F P=105>  Belarusian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Over the past two years, about 15,000 officers have 
been discharged from the Belarusian Armed Forces. These were 
basically individuals entitled to pensions or those who did not 
wish to continue their service. At the same, the number of 
officers who were born in Belarus has noticeably increased. 
While such officers used to represent 16 percent of all 
personnel in the Belarusian Armed Fores, this ratio has risen to 
47 percent today. It is estimated that with new graduates from 
the military schools joining the Armed Forces, this number will 
climb to 53-55 percent. In as little as one year, Belarus-born 
servicemen will account for 65 percent of the Belarusian Army, 
RID agency reported. 

</TEXT>

