<DOCNO> FBIS4-41124 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov120_a_94001" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-120 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  22 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Signs Partnership for Peace Program in Brussels </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozyrev Signs Partnership for Peace Program in Brussels </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2206100294 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0945 
GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2206100294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS special correspondents Dmitriy Gorokhov and </F>
Aleksandr Mineyev] 
  [Text] Brussels, 22 Jun -- Today, Russia joined the 
"Partnership for Peace" program proposed by NATO leaders. At 
the alliance's headquarters, Russia's Foreign Minister Andrey 
Kozyrev signed a framework document on the general principles of 
participation in this program, the aims of which have already 
been supported by 20 states of Central, Eastern, and Northern 
Europe. 

</TEXT>

