<H3> <TI>   Further on Kravchuk Ruling on Crimean Decrees </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Kravchuk Ruling on Crimean Decrees </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2106160994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1319 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2106160994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Kravchuk has ruled that the Crimean 
President's decrees "On the property of the Republic of Crimea" 
and "On the privatization of Crimea's state-run enterprises" 
contravene Ukraine's legislation. 
  He dismissed as illegal the declaration of Crimea's control 
over the property of state-run transportation depots, 
information and communication facilities, higher educational 
establishments and other institutions in Crimea. 
  The decree maintains that in line with Ukrainian law, this 
is 
part of the property that belongs to all in society. 
  Besides, part of what is to be privatized in accordance with 
the Crimean President Meshkov's decree relates to the national 
property of Ukraine, the decree stresses. 

</TEXT>

