<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Crimea Leader Stresses Integration of Sevastopol </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Crimea Leader Stresses Integration of Sevastopol </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2106220694 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 2100 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2106220694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sevastopol, 21 Jun -- Serhiy Tsekov, Supreme Council 
of Crimea chairman, has visited Sevastopol. He met there Black 
Sea Fleet Commander Eduard Baltin, Sevastopol City Council 
Chairman Viktor Semenov, and some Republican Movement of Crimea 
activists who are running in the election to the city council of 
the next convocation. 
  Meeting representatives of the mass media, Serhiy Tsekov 
stated that "the Supreme Council of Crimea has no problems with 
the government." At the same time he spoke against the 
president of Crimea being granted directive powers and against 
Ilma Umerov, a Crimean Tartar deputy, being appointed to the 
post of Crimea's social policy minister. 
  Serhiy Tsekov added that the city of Sevastopol should be 
fully integrated in Crimea and that "if Crimea's authorities 
fail to achieve this in a civilized manner, a decision will -- 
in the worst case -- be taken declaring Sevastopol the capital 
of Crimea." Oleksiy Melnikov, Supreme Council of Crimea deputy 
chairman, backed that opinion, saying: "If Russia does not need 
Sevastopol, Crimea does." 

</TEXT>

