<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Receives Kyrgyz Premier; Agreements Signed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Receives Kyrgyz Premier; Agreements Signed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2106145594 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Kazakh 1400 GMT 
21 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2106145594 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty Kazakh Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Kazakh </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Nursultan Nazarbayev received today 
Kyrgyzstan's Prime Minister Apas Dzhumagulov, who is on a 
working visit in Kazakhstan. Government delegations of 
Kazakhstan and Kyrgyzstan, led by Prime Ministers Tereshchenko 
and Dzumagulov had a meeting later. They discussed implementing 
the agreement on trade and economic cooperation between the two 
countries. They also discussed the issue of paying our 
republic's debt of $55 million to the neighboring state for 
power supplies. The meeting discussed prospects for cooperation 
in the joint construction of the Kumbartinskiy GES and the 
possibility of power supplies to the southern parts of 
Kazakhstan, the volume of this year's supplies of Kazakhstan's 
chemical compounds with a trace of uranium to the Karabaltinskiy 
ore mining combine. The initiative for a joint 
Kazakhstan-Kyrgyzstan venture for processing and refining raw 
materials containing uranium was supported. It was decided that 
profits from selling uranium protoxide and oxide will be split 
in the following way: Kazakhstan's works will get 71 percent and 
Kyrgyzstan's 29 percent. 
  An intergovernmental protocol on the implementation of 
agreements on trade and economic cooperation between the two 
republics for 1994 and an agreement on supplying Kyrgyzstan with 
raw materials containing uranium starting from this year up to 
the year 2,000 were signed. Tereshchenko and Dzhumagulov told 
journalists that the working visit has given a new impetus to 
trade and economic cooperation between the two countries. 

</TEXT>

