<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Opposition Stronghold `Crushed' in Garmskiy Rayon </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Opposition Stronghold `Crushed' in Garmskiy Rayon </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2106112694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1035 
GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2106112694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by unidentified ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Dushanbe, 21 Jun -- The press center of Tajikistan's 
Defense Ministry reports that in the course of troop operations 
between 7 and 17 June in Garmskiy, Tajikabadskiy, and 
Jirgitalskiy Rayons, a stronghold of Tajik opposition fighters, 
who were receiving military assistance from Afghan mojaheddin 
instructors, was crushed in the territory of the destroyed 
villages of Chevi Mangaryk. The operations were conducted 
jointly by units of the Defense, Interior, and Security 
Ministries of Tajikistan. 
  In the course of just one battle, 12 opposition fighters 
were 
killed and seven wounded, other casualty figures are being 
clarified. German and British-made radio communication 
equipment, as well as a grenade launcher, grenades, and firearm 
ammunition were seized. Fire drill notebooks in Tajik and Pashto 
and other documents belonging to the fighters were found. 
  Law-enforcement agencies detained several members of armed 
groups. Four servicemen of the Defense Ministry of Tajikistan 
were killed in the fighting and nine were wounded. Measures 
were taken during the operation to ensure the maximum safety of 
civilians from nearby villages. 
  The tasks set before the troops have been carried out. Units 
of the Armed Forces of Tajikistan have now returned to their 
sites of regular deployment. However, despite all the measures 
that are being taken by the authorities and the forces to 
stabilize the situation in the Garm group of rayons, the 
situation there remains tense. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

