<H3> <TI>   Federation Council Appeal on Duma Budget Discussion </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Federation Council Appeal on Duma Budget Discussion </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2106180294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1700 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2106180294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS parliamentary correspondent Lyudmila Yermakova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 21 TASS -- An appeal of the Russian 
Federation Council requested the State Duma today to take into 
account its opinion when discussing the draft 1994 budget in 
third reading. 
  The appeal aims to support the application of the 
Association 
of Defence Industry Trade Unions and the League for Assistance 
to the Defence Plants on the need to prevent the defence 
industry collapse, Chairman of the Federation Council Budget 
Committee Nikolay Gonchar said here today. This morning 
representatives of the defence industries picketed the 
Federation Council building, and the chairman of the Association 
of Defence Industry Trade Union's Executive Committee made a 
report on the branch crisis at the Federation Council meeting at 
the invitation of the council speaker. 
  The Federation Council offered the State Duma to revise the 
defence spending item of the budget at an amount of 55 trillion 
rubles. The lower parliament chamber is expected to discuss the 
draft budget on Wednesday. 
  The Federation Council will continue its meeting on June 22. 

</TEXT>

