<H3> <TI>   Call Made To Strip Shevardnadze of Special Powers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Call Made To Strip Shevardnadze of Special Powers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2106174394 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network in Russian 1510 
GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2106174394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Georgian parliament held a session today which 
discussed the country's budget. The parliamentary opposition 
gave a sharply negative assessment of the draft budget and took 
the opportunity to raise the issue of authority, demanding that 
the head of state be stripped of his special powers. 
  The session also heard a statement from the parliamentary 
majority, which condemns the activity of opposition deputies who 
are trying to create an obstructive atmosphere in the country's 
supreme legislative body and introduce it into the republic's 
sociopolitical life in general. The statement stresses that 
attempts by the opposition to impose on deputies a debate on the 
issue of authority, especially the issue of stripping the head 
of state of his special powers, is aimed at sowing 
destabilization in the country. The statement says that the 
issue of authority is addressed by the draft of the republic's 
new constitution and will be debated before the constitution is 
adopted. 

</TEXT>

