<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Holds News Conference on Protocol </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Holds News Conference on Protocol </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2206130294 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1111 
GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2206130294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS special correspondent Dmitriy Gorokhov and </F>
Aleksandr Mineyev] 
  [Text] Brussels, 22 Jun -- At a joint news conference with 
Andrey Kozyrev, Russian minister of foreign affairs, Sergio 
Balanzino, NATO deputy secretary general, made public a protocol 
on the fundamentals of interrelations between NATO and Russia. 
  According to the document, "Russia and NATO have agreed to 
have wide-ranging, in-depth dialogue and cooperation in those 
spheres where Russia can make a unique and important 
contribution that corresponds to its importance and 
responsibility as a great European, world, and nuclear state." 
The forms of cooperation comprise exchange of information, 
holding political consultations as necessary, and interaction on 
the whole range of security issues, including those in the 
sphere of maintaining peace. The sides agreed to prepare a 
broad individual partnership program that would correspond to 
Russia's size, importance, and potential. 

</TEXT>

