<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Churkin Warns of Large-Scale War in Former Yugoslavia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Churkin Warns of Large-Scale War in Former Yugoslavia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2306100394 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0924 
GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2306100394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS special correspondents Yuriy Sizov, Vladimir </F>
Malyshev, and Yuriy Malinov] 
  [Text] Kerkyra (Corfu), 23 Jun (ITAR-TASS) -- Russian 
Deputy Foreign Minister Vitaliy Churkin warned today of the 
danger of a "big war" breaking out in former Yugoslavia. 
Churkin, who is accompanying Russian Foreign Minister Andrey 
Kozyrev, arrived on this Greek island from Brussels today. The 
two men are to attend the signing of the agreement on 
partnership and cooperation between the Russian Federation and 
the European Union. 
  It seems to me, he said in response to questions from 
ITAR-TASS, that during July the peoples of former Yugoslavia, 
especially Bosnia, have their last chance to reach agreement. 
If this chance is missed, a big war will result. V. Churkin 
suggested that this big war could start as soon as the summer 
ends. He disclosed that proposals for a settlement of the 
Bosnian crisis which were "unprecedentedly" resolute were about 
to be discussed. If these proposals are not accepted during 
July, a great calamity will result, he said. 

</TEXT>

