<H3> <TI>   Kondratyev Leaves for Abkhazia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kondratyev Leaves for Abkhazia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2206124794 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 1100 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2206124794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The peacekeeping operation in the Georgian-Abkhaz 
conflict zone will start 26 June, Colonel-General Grigoriy 
Kondratyev, Russia's deputy minister of defense, told INTERFAX. 
  Kondratyev set off for the region today to take personal 
charge of the peacekeeping mission. Grigoriy Kondratyev said 
that five Russian battalions totalling 2,500-3,000 servicemen 
are being brought in for the operation. According to him, two 
battalions from Batumi have already started moving with their 
equipment into the area separating the warring sides. 
  The deputy minister also said that military transport 
aircraft and helicopters started loading the personnel and 
equipment of two battalions of paratroopers today. Tomorrow, 
that is, Thursday, the battalions from the Ulyanovsk paratroop 
division will start leaving for the conflict zone. 

</TEXT>

