<H3> <TI>   Belarusian Presidential Candidate Arrives in Moscow </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Belarusian Presidential Candidate Arrives in Moscow </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2206123494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1016 
GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2206123494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tamara Zamyatina] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 22 Jun -- With presidential elections in 
Belarus being just a day away, one of the leading candidates 
Vyacheslav Kebich, chairman of republican council of ministers, 
has arrived in Moscow. A meeting between Vyacheslav Kebich and 
First Deputy Prime Minister Oleg Soskovets is on the list of 
today's activities for Russia's top government officials. 
  The Russian government office is not saying much about the 
content of the meeting which took place behind closed doors. 
One can assert that the Russian Cabinet of Ministers likes one 
of the election promises of the Belarusian prime minister, 
namely his intention to introduce "tax holidays" for Russian 
goods which are not going to be taxed. 
  It is thought that Vyacheslav Kebich will be received in the 
Kremlin since Boris Yeltsin made it clear at a press conference 
on 10 June that Russia is "very much" interested in the Belarus 
election results. It is obvious who Russia would like to see as 
the head of Belarus. 

</TEXT>

