<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Lukyanov Comments on Belarus Conference on Cooperation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lukyanov Comments on Belarus Conference on Cooperation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2206121394 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1005 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2206121394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A deputy of the Russian State Duma, ex-chairman of 
the USSR (Union of Soviet Socialist Republics) Supreme Soviet 
Anatoliy Lukyanov said he believed that there was no alternative 
to a renewed Union. 
  On Tuesday he took part in the meeting in the Belarussian 
Academy of Geo-Politics which was holding an international 
conference "Russia and Belarus - the way to the future" in 
Minsk. 
  Lukyanov told Interfax that his visit to Minsk was aimed at 
expressing support to those forces standing for expansion of 
Russian-Belarussian cooperation and defending the idea of 
restoration of a renewed Union. 
  "My visit has absolutely nothing to do with the coming 
presidential elections in Belarus," Lukyanov stressed. 
  He said that the mechanism for restoration of the Union was 
created when 19 communist parties were set up in the ex- Soviet 
republics. Lukyanov said that the congress of the USSR peoples 
planned for this September was also expected to contribute to 
establishment of a mass movement for restoration of the Union. 
  Lukyanov spoke in favor of participation of Russian and 
Belarussian parliamentarians in the hearings on the results of 
the implementation of the Belaya Vezh agreement which will be 
held in the State Duma Committee on CIS in early July. 

</TEXT>

