<H3> <TI>   U.S. Sees Russia as Conduit for Illegal Migrants From PRC </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Sees Russia as Conduit for Illegal Migrants From PRC </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2306094194 Moscow KOMSOMOLSKAYA PRAVDA in Russian 22 Jun 
94 p 2 </F>

<F P=103> PM2306094194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KOMSOMOLSKAYA PRAVDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Andrey Kabannikov: "Chinese Mafiosi Have Begun </F>
To Speak Russian"] 
  [Text] Beijing -- U.S. State Department specialists 
studying the problem of illegal immigration consider that Russia 
has become a new center for the Chinese mafia's activities. 
They estimate that around 60,000 Chinese are presently waiting 
their turn to cross over to the countries of Europe and America 
from Russia. 
  But the Americans complain that it is difficult to work with 
the Russian authorities as the latter show no interest in this 
problem. Russian border guards are easily bought off and they 
agree to let illegal immigrants through the border. Nobody 
wants to be involved in sending immigrants back to China. State 
Department representatives are going to discuss these problems 
in the next few days with their Russian colleagues in Moscow. 

</TEXT>

