<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Nazarbayev Resolution on Supporting Entrepreneurship </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nazarbayev Resolution on Supporting Entrepreneurship </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2206192994 Almaty KAZTAG in Russian 1430 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2206192994 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty KAZTAG </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Resolution by Kazakh President Nazarbayev on the 
state program for supporting and encouraging entrepreneurship in 
the Republic of Kazakhstan for 1994-96: 
  In accordance with the Resolution No. 1655 of the Republic 
of 
Kazakhstan of 13 April 1994 "On the State Commission of the 
Republic of Kazakhstan for Supporting and Encouraging 
Entrepreneurship," I decree: 
  1. To approve the state program for supporting and 
encouraging entrepreneurship in the Republic of Kazakhstan in 
1994-96. (enclosed [KAZTAG note; not further explained]) 
  2. The Cabinet of Ministers of the Republic of Kazakhstan 
should take the nessessary steps to fulfill the state program 
for supporting and encouraging entrepreneurship in the Republic 
of Kazakhstan in 1994-96, and within two weeks it should 
elaborate on and endorse a draft plan of measures and tasks 
aimed at implementing the program. If necessary, it should make 
annual adjustments to the plan of measures and tasks aimed at 
implementing the program. 
  3. Heads of regional, Almaty, and Leninsk city 
administrations should elaborate on specific measures aimed at 
implementing the state program for supporting and encouraging 
entrepreneurship in the Republic of Kazakhstan in 1994-96, which 
will take into consideration regional characteristics. 
  [Signed] President Nazarbayev Almaty, 
  [Dated] 10 June 1994. 

</TEXT>

