<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Reacts to Article in Russian Newspaper </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry Reacts to Article in Russian Newspaper </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2206195694 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Russian 1400 GMT 
22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2206195694 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty Kazakh Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Foreign Ministry noted an article published 
recently in [name indistinct] a Russian newspaper titled "Russia 
Has Become a Testing Site for Exotic Spies." It contains a 
reference to a statement made by Baturin, assistant to the 
Russian president on national security, who doubted the ability 
of our republic to control its borders properly with China. The 
Foreign Ministry press service is obligated to inform relevant 
parties that in accordance with the information given by 
reliable sources, illegal attempts to cross the border are not 
numerous. Transgressors are usually always detained. As far as 
border control is concerned, a visa agreement on traveling 
between Kazakhstan and China, which envisages the need for 
exit-entry visas for trips by citizens of both Kazakhstan and 
China, was concluded. Such conclusions on the ability of an 
independent country to defend its borders should be based on 
facts, the more so because the Republic's relevant services 
exchange border information on a regular basis with the 
leadership of the Russian border troops. 

</TEXT>

