<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Illegal Rally' Demands Resignation of Oblast Officials </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Illegal Rally' Demands Resignation of Oblast Officials </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2206125594 Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network in Russian 
0400 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2206125594 </F>
<F P=104>  Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Resignation of the officials of the Gorno-Badakhshan 
Autonomous Oblast of Tajikistan was demanded by the participants 
of a small illegal rally, which took place in Khorog, the 
administrative center of the oblast. 
  A correspondent of the ITAR-TASS news agency was told this 
by 
an independent and well-informed source of Gorno-Badakhshan. 
  The demonstrators, among whom were many women and old 
people, 
accused the local authorities of being unable to end legal 
tyranny and the growth of organized crime. 
  The demonstrators pointed out that the processes of 
surrendering weapons, which are illegally kept by the 
population, and the disbanding of illegal armed formations are 
extremely slow in Khorog as well as in other rayons of the 
autonomous oblast. [words indistinct] 
  Saydamir Zukhurov, minister of security, confirmed the 
report 
on illegal rally in Khorog. However, according to his words 
there were no demands of resignation of the oblast's leadership. 
The people wanted to learn from the officials of 
Gorno-Badakhshan Autonomous Oblast when law and order finally 
would be established on the territory of the autonomous oblast 
and after receiving full and specific answers the demonstrators 
peacefully went away, stated Zukhurov, minister of security of 
Tajikistan. 

</TEXT>

