<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   North Ossetia, Ingushetia Reject Refugee Plan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    North Ossetia, Ingushetia Reject Refugee Plan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2206134194 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0900 GMT 
22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2206134194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Representatives of North Ossetia and Ingushetia have 
both turned down options for the return of refugees to their 
former homes, which had been put to both sides. The RIA news 
agency was informed of this today by negotiators representing 
the interim administration in the state of emergency zone. 
  The interim administration has drawn up its own proposals, 
which are now being worked on by state structures in both 
republics. The details of the plan have not been divulged so 
far. However, RIA has learned from reliable sources that the 
interim administration intends to abide by the timetable and 
principles for the return of refugees set out in the Russian 
president's decree of 30 May this year. 

</TEXT>

