<H3> <TI>   Panel To Draft Treaty With Bashkortostan Named </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Panel To Draft Treaty With Bashkortostan Named </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2306095194 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 22 Jun 94 
First Edition p 4 </F>

<F P=103> PM2306095194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Russian Federation Presidential Directive No. 300-d, signed </F>
by President Yeltsin and dated 14 June 1994] 
  [Text] A commission to draw up a draft bilateral treaty on 
the demarcation of areas of responsibility [predmety vedeniya] 
and the reciprocal delegation of powers between organs of state 
power in the Russian Federation and the Republic of 
Bashkortostan is to be set up with the following members: 
  S.M. Shakhray, deputy chairman of the Russian Federation 
Government, commission leader; 
  R.G. Abdulatipov, deputy chairman of the Russian Federation 
Federal Assembly Federation Council (by agreement) [po 
soglasovaniyu]; 
  S.A. Shapovalov, chairman of the Russian Federation Federal 
Assembly State Duma Committee for Federation Affairs and 
Regional Policy (by agreement); 
  A.G. Shapovalyants, Russian Federation deputy minister of 
economics; 
  A.M. Pozdnyakov, Russian Federation deputy minister for 
nationalities affairs and regional policy; 
  A.V. Maslov, deputy head of the Russian Federation 
president's State Legal Administration; 
  A.P. Kozlov, head of the Russian Federation Government 
Apparatus's Department for Cooperation with Russian Federation 
Regions; 
  V.A. Pechenev, deputy head of the Russian Federation 
Presidential Staff Administration for Work with the Territories. 
  [Signed] Russian Federation President B. Yeltsin 
  [Dated] 14 June 1994 
  No. 300-d 

</TEXT>

