<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   St Petersburg Administrative Reorganization Planned </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    St Petersburg Administrative Reorganization Planned </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2306102194 Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI in Russian 23 Jun 94 p 
2 </F>

<F P=103> PM2306102194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Three Rayons Instead of Seven"] </F>
  [Text] A reorganization of the organs of executive power 
is taking place in St. Petersburg. It is aimed at improving the 
work of the rayon link and reducing the number of officials in 
these structures. The city's administrative division has 
changed: Three rayons -- Admiralteyskiy, Kurortnyy, and 
Tsentralnyy -- have been organized on the basis of seven rayons. 
  Work is under way on the formation of the concept of local 
self-management. For this a directive from the mayor has formed 
a working group consisting of workers from the city hall and 
rayon administrations and representatives of the public. 

</TEXT>

