<H3> <TI>   Shevardnadze Hails Russian Peacekeeping Mission </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shevardnadze Hails Russian Peacekeeping Mission </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Stresses Importance of Solution </H4>

<F P=102> NC2206200294 Yerevan SNARK in English 1247 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2206200294 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tbilisi, June 22 (SNARK) -- "If we manage to achieve 
a considerable progress in cause of Abkhazian conflict's 
settlement, a process of general stabilization in Caucasian 
region will begin", declared Eduard Shevardnadze in his 
interview to SNARK. 
  Answering the question on the ways of the Karabakh problem's 
settlement, the Head of Georgian State mentioned that the 
Abkhazian conflict's settlement will be a great spur for solving 
all the conflicts in Transcaucasia with the participation of 
Russia. 
  "The form of the Abkhazian conflict's settlement is unique 
and it will be a good example in searching the ways of solving 
the Karabakh conflict", said the Head of Georgian State. 

</TEXT>

