<H3> <TI>   Defense Ministry Reorganizes; Deputy Ministers Appointed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Ministry Reorganizes; Deputy Ministers Appointed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2206184894 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network in Georgian 1500 
GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2206184894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network </F>
<F P=105>  Georgian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The CONTACT news agency provided us with information 
from the Defense Ministry press center that work is continuing 
to reduce the Defense Ministry's structure and improve its 
efficiency. Several deputy defense minister positions were 
abolished. A new position of first deputy defense minister of 
the Republic of Georgia was created, who is to be responsible 
for rear front construction and troop disposition [zurgis 
mshenebloba da jarebis gantavseba]. 
  By a decree of the Georgian head of state, Colonel Razhden 
Bitsadze has been appointed first deputy defense minister of the 
Republic of Georgia responsible for rear front construction and 
troop disposition. 
  By a decree of the head of state, Major General Giorgiy 
Vashakidze has been appointed deputy defense minister of the 
Republic of Georgia. 
  By a decree of the head of state, Maj. Gen. Boris Ivanov has 
been appointed head of the Army Service Department [sajariso 
samsakhuris gankopileba] of the General Staff of the Defense 
Ministry of the Republic of Georgia. 

</TEXT>

