<H3> <TI>   Abkhaz Foreign Ministry Against `Mass' Return of Refugees </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Abkhaz Foreign Ministry Against `Mass' Return of Refugees </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2206181494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1555 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2206181494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Any mass return of Georgian refugees to Abkhazia 
during the peacekeeping operation in the region will be 
unacceptable, the Abkhazian foreign ministry said in a statement 
on Wednesday. It said the measure would be enforced on a 
case-by-case basis in keeping with the program adopted by the 
four- party commission. 
  The commission, now into a second day of work at the Black 
Sea city of Sochi, involves representatives of Russia, Georgia, 
Abkhazia and the United Nations. The timing and procedure of 
repatriating the refugees and displaced persons dominates its 
agenda. 
  The ministry has spoken against any attempt to try to link 
the deployment of Russian peacekeepers in the region with the 
repatriation issue. 

</TEXT>

