<H3> <TI>   Procuracy To Seek Compromise </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Procuracy To Seek Compromise </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2306100994 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 0800 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2306100994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] In the General Procuracy in Moscow today, an 
expanded meeting of the collegium is taking place. It is 
discussing measures aimed at intensifying the fight against 
crime. Those taking part in the collegium sitting are the 
procurators of republics, krays and oblasts, heads of all the 
federal law enforcement bodies, security councils of Russia, 
senior staff of the president and the government, 
representatives of both houses of the Federal Assmebly, and law 
experts. As ITAR-TASS learned from competent sources, the 
General Procuracy will also try to stir the participants to seek 
compromise regarding the enforcement of the president's edict of 
14 June, until the legislative bodies adopt necessary laws. 

