<H3> <TI>   Major Anti-Crime Operation Conducted in Moscow </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Major Anti-Crime Operation Conducted in Moscow </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2206211994 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 1700 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2206211994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Our television agency received interesting 
information today from the public relations center of the 
Ministry of Internal Affairs, which we give almost in full. 
  On 21 June, operatives from the Moscow city directorate of 
internal affairs--with the support of 20,000 men of the 
Dzerzhinskiy Motor Rifle Division of interior troops--carried 
out a citywide preventive operation code-named Hurricane. In 24 
hours, the special service visited 689 sites. Of these, 14 
hotels, the offices of 232 commercial structures and banks, and 
four markets were inspected. At 27 parking lots and 43 main 
vehicle inspectorate checkpoints, 1,053 motor vehicles were 
inspected. 
  A total of 2,251 people were detained for investigation. 
Administrative proceedings have been instituted against 759 of 
them. The operations of 193 commercial structures have been 
suspended. A total of 292 crimes were registered, and 219 were 
solved. Twenty-three previously stolen vehicles were found. 

</TEXT>

