<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Majority Believe Rise of Fascism Possible </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Majority Believe Rise of Fascism Possible </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2206144194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1315 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2206144194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The All-Russia Public Opinion Center held an opinion 
poll among 1594 respondents on the eve of June 22 which marks 
the 53rd anniversary of fascist Germany's attack on the Soviet 
Union. Forty-seven percent of Russian citizens believe that the 
rise of fascism is quite possible in Russia, while 35 percent 
have the opposite opinion. Eighteen percent of the respondents 
were undecided. 
  Seventy-five percent of those polled said that fascist 
organizations must be banned and 8 percent that such 
organizations have the right to exist. Five percent of the 
respondents think there are no and will be no such organizations 
in this country. Seven percent of the respondents were undecided 
and 5 percent said that this problem did not interest them. 
  Eighty-one percent of those poled believe that June 22 must 
be declared a day of national mourning and memory for the 
victims of the War. Seven percent were against this idea. 
Seven percent were undecided and 5 percent were not interested 
in the problem. 

</TEXT>

