<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin To Sign Follow-Up Privatization Program </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin To Sign Follow-Up Privatization Program </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK2206063094 Moscow SEGODNYA in Russian 22 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> MK2206063094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow SEGODNYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [INTERFAX report: "Post-Check Privatization Draft Program </F>
Will Be Submitted to President Friday"] 
  [Text] A draft state program of post-check [voucher] 
privatization setting out the rules for denationalization of 
state property after 1 July will probably be up for President 
Boris Yeltsin's signature Friday. This has been disclosed by 
Dmitriy Vasilyev, deputy chairman of the Russian Federation 
State Committee for the Management of State Property. According 
to him, an edict setting the state program in motion is supposed 
to be signed by Boris Yeltsin early next week. Russian 
Federation Vice Premier Anatoliy Chubays stated earlier that 
some 20 percent of state property is supposed to be privatized 
for money in the post-check period. By July 1994 70 percent of 
Russia's property will be in the private sector; 10 percent of 
state enterprises are not subject to privatization. 

</TEXT>

