<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gerashchenko Foresees No Upsurge in Inflation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gerashchenko Foresees No Upsurge in Inflation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2306104894 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0943 
GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2306104894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 23 Jun (BUSINESS-TASS) -- Russian Central 
Bank chairman Viktor Gerashchenko believes that one should not 
expect an upsurge in inflation in Russia during the second 
quarter of this year. 
  A rough analysis of the economic situation, he said today, 
shows that the government guidelines on money supply for the 
second quarter will be observed. According to available 
information, over the first four months of this year, the 
average monthly growth rate of the money supply was 10 percent 
while growth in cash supply was 13 percent, which is within the 
established targets. 
  Viktor Gerashchenko was giving a report on the results of 
the 
Russian Bank in 1993 and current tasks at a conference with 
heads of the main territorial directorates (national banks). 
The main aim of the conference, in which representatives of the 
State Duma and of the staffs of the president and government of 
the Russian Federation are also taking part, is to discover the 
main problems in the work of the Central Bank system and to 
define solutions to them. 

</TEXT>

