<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Signs Decree on Use of Border Troops </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Signs Decree on Use of Border Troops </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2206210694 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1900 GMT 
22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2206210694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Boris Yeltsin has signed a decree on Russian 
servicemen as border troops taking part in work based on the 
international legal demarcation of the state border of the 
Russian Federation. This has been reported by the president's 
press service. In accordance with the document, border troops 
engaged in this work are being sent to carry out their military 
service to a department of the international legal demarcation 
of the state border, which is being set up within the Main 
Command of Border Troops. The decree provides for measures for 
the social protection of the servicemen during their transfer to 
the new department. 

