<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on `Topol' Training Launch </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on `Topol' Training Launch </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2206162494 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 1400 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2206162494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] We have just received a special report from the town 
of Plesetsk on a command and staff military exercise. As we 
have already reported, Russian President Boris Yeltsin and 
Defense Minister Pavel Grachev monitored [kontrolirovali] the 
exercise. 
  [Correspondent Mikhail Zotov] During the command and staff 
exercise of strategic missile troops in the area of test range 
No. 53 in Plesetsk today, a training launch of the Topol 
strategic intercontinental solid fuel missile was carried out. 
Its projected target area was Kamchatka. Adjacent countries 
were informed about the planned launch, and the flight of the 
missile was tracked by nine ground radars, which transmitted the 
data to a computer center in Plesetsk. The Russian defense 
minister and the commander in chief monitored the exercise. 
  In the opinion of military observers, the 100-tonne, RS-12M 
Topol launcher has shown once again the reliability and high 
quality of operation of all the systems and of the missile 
launch crew. Despite the fact that the strategic missile troops 
are experiencing many of the problems that are characteristic of 
the Army, the strategic missile troops still remain a reliable 
guarantor of Russia's security and independence. 
  The number of training launches, however, is dwindling with 
each passing year. The families of the servicemen who have 
decided to give up the difficult job of officer in the Russian 
Army are leaving the garrisons. For the time being, a few 35- 
or 40-year-old officers, who have not given up the protection of 
Russian borders in a difficult moment, ensure the combat 
training of missile troops. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

