<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aliyev Meeting With Cuban Official Detailed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aliyev Meeting With Cuban Official Detailed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2206190394 Baku Azerbaycan Radio Televiziyasi Television 
Network in Azeri 1600 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2206190394 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku Azerbaycan Radio Televiziyasi Television 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Azeri </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Azerbaijani President Geydar Aliyev received Cuban 
Deputy Prime Minister Lionel Soto on 21 June. 
  [Reporter Sakit Ocakli] Matters of mutual concern to both 
states were touched upon during the meeting. The guest conveyed 
Cuban leader Fidel Castro's greetings to Geydar Aliyev, and 
invited the president to pay an official visit to Cuba whenever 
he wanted. The Azerbaijani president thanked him for the sincere 
invitation, indicated that he has great respect for the Cuban 
leader Fidel Castro and the Cuban people, and in his turn 
invited the Cuban leaders, the Fidel and Raul Castro brothers, 
to visit Azerbaijan. 
  Geydar Aliyev briefed the guest on the developments in 
Azerbaijan in recent years, especially on Armenia's occupation 
of Azerbaijani soil. He added that the international 
organizations, particularly the CSCE and the Minsk Group, are 
trying to find a peaceful resolution to the conflict. Geydar 
Aliyev said that our brave sons, who are defending their 
motherland and waging a struggle for the indivisibility of the 
homeland, are courageously facing the enemy. 
  The guest said that Cuban society knows about the Karabakh 
conflict, and the members of the Cuban delegation indicated 
that, moved by the adage that you find out who are your true 
friends when times get tough, they are ready to help Azerbaijan 
in every way. 
  Matters pertaining to cooperation between the two states 
were 
broached during the meeting. 

</TEXT>

