<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bread Shortage Continues Despite Grain Shipment </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bread Shortage Continues Despite Grain Shipment </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2206140694 Baku TURAN in English 1127 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2206140694 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baku (June 21) TURAN--Although the prices for bread 
were increased, the bread deficit in Azerbaijan still remains. 
The State Concern for bread products told TURAN that grain 
deliveries are delayed due to tension at the North-Caucasian 
railway. 
  The same source also said that 200 cars with grain 
travelling 
to Azerbaijan are presently at that railway. 
  On June 17 Turkey shipped 24,000 tons of grain to 
Azerbaijan. 
According to specialists, this grain delivery is unable to solve 
bread deficit in the country where every-day need in bread 
totals more than 2,000 tons. 
  An employee of the State Concern for bread products said 
that 
those who live in villages come to Baku to buy bread since, 
actually, bread is not delivered to Azerbaijani republics 
[plural as received]. This fact worsens the bread deficit in 
Azerbaijan as well. 

</TEXT>

