<H3> <TI>   Chisinau, Kiev Representatives To Discuss Border Issues </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chisinau, Kiev Representatives To Discuss Border Issues </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2206201594 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 2055 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2206201594 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chisinau, BASAPRESS, 18/6/1994 -- A meeting of the 
departments of foreign relations experts from the Ukraine and 
Moldova is to be held at the end of July. The meeting will 
discuss issues concerning the frontiers between the two states, 
declared to BASA a representative of the Moldovan Ministry of 
Foreign Affairs (MAE). Initially, the Ukrainian MAE suggested 
the meeting to be organized at the end of June, but the Chisinau 
officials requested it to be postponed for a month, for they 
wanted better to prepare for it. The cited source stated that a 
visit to Kiev by the vice-premier Valentin Cunev was scheduled 
for the first half of June. Cunev was to discuss issues 
concerning interstate collaboration in the fields of 
transportation, economics, and exploitation of sea vacation 
houses. The visit was postponed because the new Ukrainian 
chamber of ministers was not yet formed. 

</TEXT>

