<H3> <TI>   Romanian Government Delegation Visits Chisinau </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Romanian Government Delegation Visits Chisinau </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2306072794 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 2055 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2306072794 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chisinau, BASAPRESS, 18/6/1994 -- A Romanian 
Governmental delegation, led by the head of the Direction for 
Relations with Moldova of the Romanian Ministry of Foreign 
Affairs and secretary of the Romanian Inter Ministry Committee, 
Gheorghe Savuica, visited Chisinau this week. The visit was 
made according to the agreement signed at the reunion of the 
Romanian and Moldova Inter Ministry committees held 15 February 
in Bucharest. Dorin Cimpoiesu, first secretary of the Romanian 
Embassy to Chisinau, stated to BASA that the purpose of this 
visit was to analyze progress regarding economic integration and 
consolidation of the common spiritual area and to prepare new 
projects for future joint reunions to be held in Chisinau. The 
Romanian delegation met with Governmental representatives. 
Cimpoiesu pointed out that the secretaries of the two Inter 
Ministry Committees met with the management of the sanitation 
equipment plant in Falesti and TEPRO plant in Iasi to discuss 
the common project of constructing a pipeline. 

