<H3> <TI>   Masol, U.S. Envoy Discuss Economic Issues </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Masol, U.S. Envoy Discuss Economic Issues </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2206210194 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1800 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2206210194 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 22 June, Prime Minister Vitaliy Masol received 
U.S. Ambassador William Green Miller at his request. During a 
sincere conversation touching on a broad range of issues, they 
deeply analyzed the state of Ukrainian-U.S. relations in the 
field of economic cooperation. The ambassador was informed 
about the economic and social problems facing the Government of 
Ukraine today and about ways to reform the economy taking into 
account the approaches expounded by the prime minister during 
the confirmation of his appointment by the Supreme Council. 
  They also discussed the implementation of the agreements on 
economic assistance to Ukraine -- first and foremost, in 
organizing the production of medical preparations and on 
financial support for entrepreneurship. Issues pertaining to 
the forthcoming discussion by the G-7 leaders regarding energy 
supplies for Ukraine were also discussed, in particular, on 
providing help in developing and improving the safety of nuclear 
power engineering. 
  Ukraine's Foreign Minister Anatoliy Zlenko took part in the 
conversation. 

</TEXT>

