<H3> <TI>   Ambassador to Belarus Urges Stepping Up Relations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ambassador to Belarus Urges Stepping Up Relations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2306010494 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1900 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2306010494 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev -- As a UNIAN correspondent learned on 22 June, 
Ukraine's Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary to the 
Republic of Belarus Volodymyr Zheliba sent a letter to Ukraine's 
Prime Minister Vitaliy Masol. The letter, in particular, 
indicates that for Belarus, Ukraine ranks second, following 
Russia, as far as foreign political aspect is concerned, and 
expresses concern at the state of Ukrainian-Belarusian 
relations, at the absence of contacts at the top state level, 
and also absence of proper trade and economic relations. 
  "We are convinced that the state of bilateral cooperation 
must be considered at the high governmental level in the very 
near future," believes Volodymyr Zheliba. 
  The letter also says that Ukraine occupies the second place 
(14.9 percent), following Russia (69 percent), in trade and 
economic relations with Belarus, however the establishment of a 
joint trade house has been put off. No agreement has been 
concluded between the banks on mutual settlements and credit 
relations. Also, in the opinion of the Belarusian side, the 
issue of liabilities between our states remains unsettled. 

</TEXT>

