<F P=106> [Report under the "NEGA Reports" rubric: "Crimea"] </F>
  [Text] A sitting of the Crimean Supreme Soviet Presidium 
has taken place [date not given]. The Presidium examined a 
draft law entitling parliament to overrule edicts of Crimea's 
president and disband local soviets in the event of violation of 
the Constitution of the Republic of Crimea. The 22 June session 
of the Supreme Soviet of Crimea will consider five recent edicts 
of the president of Crimea to see if they are in line with 
Republic of Crimea legislation. The next plenary sitting will 
concern itself with the question of immediate measures to 
stabilize the agro-industrial complex of the Republic of Crimea. 

</TEXT>

