<DOCNO> FBIS4-41280 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov121_p_94005" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-121 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  22 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Relatively Peaceful Situation at Front Lines Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Relatively Peaceful Situation at Front Lines Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2206192894 Yerevan Radio Yerevan in Azeri 1330 GMT 22 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2206192894 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan Radio Yerevan </F>
<F P=105>  Azeri </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Nagorno-Karabakh Defense Army Headquarters 
reports that the situation on the Karabakh front line has not 
changed. there were no serious incidents over the past day. 
However, Azerbaijan's military forces fired on the Armenian 
defense positions with various types of arms from time to time. 
The Armenian side refrained from returning the fire. 
  No serious incidents occurred on the border between Armenia 
and Azerbaijan during the past day. The situation is relatively 
peaceful. However, it is difficult to predict how long the 
peaceful situation will continue. Everything depends on 
Azerbaijan. As a rule, Azerbaijan's aggressive operations cause 
serious incidents in the region. The Armenian side continues to 
heed the cease-fire agreement along the border. 

</TEXT>

