<F P=100> BALTIC STATES </F>
<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Laar Comments on Yeltsin Border Decree </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Laar Comments on Yeltsin Border Decree </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2206161094 Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network in Estonian 1500 
GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2206161094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network </F>
<F P=105>  Estonian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Mart Laar, commenting today on 
Russian President Boris Yeltsin's decree of 21 June on Russia 
unilaterally demarcating the Estonian-Russian state border, said 
that this is an unprecedented case internationally. According 
to the prime minister, it is particularly regrettable that this 
step was taken at a time when talks between Estonian and Russian 
representatives are in progress. Laar thinks that this is 
probably a case of Russia putting pressure on Estonia in order 
to achieve concessions with regard to resolving the issue of 
Russian military pensioners who live here. 
  At the same time, Laar stated that Estonia will firmly 
retain 
her position and continue to call for the Russian troop 
withdrawal by 31 August of this year. Estonia will definitely 
approach international organizations in order to resolve the 
conflict that has resulted from this strained situation, Laar 
emphasized. 

</TEXT>

