<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Protocol on Diplomatic Relations Signed With Nicaragua </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2206191494 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1500 GMT 22 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2206191494 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>
<F P=105>  Latvian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Latvian Foreign Ministry reports that the 
authorized representatives of Latvia and Nicaragua in New York 
have signed a protocol on establishing diplomatic relations at 
the ambassadorial level. The signatories expressed the 
conviction that it will promote and strengthen cooperation 
between the two countries in diplomatic, interparliamentary, 
economic relations, and in the cultural sphere. 
  The protocol was signed by Aivars Baumanis, Latvia's 
permanent representative to the United Nations, and Erich Asher, 
the permanent representative of Nicaragua to the United Nations. 

</TEXT>

