<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry on `Concern' Over Yeltsin Decree </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry on `Concern' Over Yeltsin Decree </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2406073294 Vilnius ELTA in English 1813 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2406073294 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius ELTA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From "News Bulletin" No. 528 ] </F>
  [Text] Vilnius, June 23, ELTA -- Department for 
Information and Media at the Lithuanian Foreign Ministry has 
distributed the following statement. 
  President of Russian Federation Boris Yeltsin June 21 has 
signed the decree "On Demarcation of Borders Between the Russian 
Federation and Estonian Republic". On this basis the Russia is 
going to demarcate the border between the states unilaterally. 
  Foreign Ministry of Lithuania expresses concern about such a 
position of Russia that contradicts the requirements of the 
European Security and Cooperation Conference to strive for 
agreements by means of negotiations, without any pressure. 
  The Ministry encourages Russia to abstain from unilateral 
actions which could threaten the stability in the region. 

</TEXT>

