<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Landsbergis on Importance of Clinton Riga Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Landsbergis on Importance of Clinton Riga Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2406103094 Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network in Lithuanian 
0900 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2406103094 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network </F>
<F P=105>  Lithuanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The forthcoming visit to Riga by U.S. President Bill 
Clinton may become an important political event strengthening 
the international security of the three Baltic states, says a 
statement by right-wing opposition leader Vytautas Landsbergis 
which was made public today. Lithuania should support the 
positions of Latvia and Estonia in two separate and not linked 
issues: a speedy and unconditional withdrawal of Russian troops 
and a citizenship law, Vytautas Landsbergis notes. 
  As is known, the Presidents of the United States and the 
Baltic states are to meet in Riga 6 July. 
  In Landsbergis's opinion, at this meeting Lithuania should 
ensure support for its government's stand, which is supported by 
the Seimas opposition, that Russia's demands to conclude a 
bilateral military transit treaty with Lithuania are political 
and should be rejected as contrary to the provisions of the 
Lithuanian Constitution and Lithuania's national interests. 
According to Vytautas Landsbergis, it is also very important to 
know whether the principles of equal rights and opportunities in 
the relations of states with NATO are still being adhered to, or 
whether the West will be drawn into an Orwellian world where one 
NATO partner is (?more equal) than the others. 

</TEXT>

