<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Calls Accord `Historic Step' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Calls Accord `Historic Step' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2406091494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0840 
GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2406091494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS special correspondents Yuriy Sizov and </F>
Vladimir Malyshev] 
  [Text] Kerkira (Corfu), 24 Jun -- "We benefit from this 
agreement," Russian President Boris Yeltsin said on the Greek 
island of Kerkira where he signed today an important document -- 
the agreement on partnership and cooperation between Russia and 
the European Union. Speaking to journalists immediately after 
the signing ceremony, he said that we are enter free trade in 
Europe as equals without any discrimination which existed in the 
past and which continues to exist in some other countries 
outside Europe. Therefore, it is a wise and strong move by the 
European community, by all its leaders and heads of state. The 
Russian president stressed: I think that a historic step has 
been made today which will not permit an economic cold war. 

</TEXT>

