<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Stresses Cooperation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Stresses Cooperation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2306213194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 2055 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2306213194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Yuriy Sizov and Vladimir </F>
Malyshev] 
  [Text] Kerkyra June 23 TASS -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin declared on Thursday that an agreement on partnership 
and cooperation between the Russian Federation and the European 
Union belongs to major and significant events in the European 
political life. Yeltsin spoke at a dinner given in honor of 
heads of countries of the European Union and the Russian 
president by the Greek Prime Minister Andreas Papandreou. 
  "We have been led to an agreement which will be signed 
tomorrow, by a sense of responsibility for the future of Europe 
and a great desire to give our children a more peaceful, more 
stable and free continent," he said. "This document opens new 
possibilities for the construction of genuinely integral, 
prosperous and safe Europe which plays an important positive 
role in the world of the 21st Century," Yeltsin said. 
  "The main task now is to realise the agreement as soon as 
possible and with the maximum result," the Russian president 
said. "It is in the interests of both Russia and the European 
Union - two largest political and economic centers of Europe, 
two powerful trade and economic partners. We shall imminently 
have to resolve problems which we have failed to resolve until 
now," he pointed out. 
  Speaking about concrete tasks which will have to be resolved 
in the near future, Yeltsin noted that it will be necessary to 
give Russia an access to the European Investment Bank and begin 
to unconditionally apply GATT norms and rules in mutual trade. 
It is necessary to facilitate visa regime for Russian citizens 
in EC countries, he added. 
  According to the Russian president, lifting restrictions on 
Russian goods in the EC market is of tremendous importance for 
the success of democratic transformations and market reforms in 
Russia. In his opinion, "the agreement lays a good basis for 
this." Yeltsin expressed confidence that the development of 
large-scale cooperation with Russia will give considerable 
advantages to states of the European Union. "This is a way to 
stepping up economic activities, the solution of social problems 
and primarily, the problem of unemployment," the Russian 
president said. 

</TEXT>

