<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovskiy Wants Russia-NATO PFP Document Annulled </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zhirinovskiy Wants Russia-NATO PFP Document Annulled </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2306201894 Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy in Russian 
1800 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2306201894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vladimir Zhirinovskiy intends to have the document 
on Russia's participation in the NATO PFP [Partnership for 
Peace] program annulled. According to the leader of the LDPR 
[Liberal Democratic Party of Russia], the document has no legal 
force. Zhirinovskiy again confirmed that he will demand the 
resignation of Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev, in this 
case, for signing the framework document with NATO. Kozyrev had 
no right to sign this program since the State Duma was 
categorically against, Zhirinovskiy said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

