<H4>    White House Releases Details </H4>

<F P=102> LD2306212294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 2054 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2306212294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Igor Borisenko, Igor Barsukov, </F>
and Pavel Vanichkin] 
  [Text] Washington June 24 TASS -- On Thursday, U.S. 
President Bill Clinton received Russian Prime Minister Viktor 
Chernomyrdin who is at the head of the Russian delegation at a 
session of the joint Russo-American commission on economic and 
technological cooperation. 
  The meeting took place in the White House behind closed 
doors. According to White House press secretary Dee Dee Myers, 
the two parties paid most attention to the results of the third 
session of the so-called "Gore-Chernomyrdin" commission and to 
the agreements which were worked out during the session. 
  President Clinton expressed satisfaction with the way 
Russia's economic reforms develop, and the United States were 
concerned about their fate in the end of 1993 and in the 
beginning of 1994, she said. 
  Asked whether Clinton and Chernomyrdin discussed a definite 
date for the forthcoming Russo-American summit in Washington 
which has been provisionally scheduled for next September, the 
press secretary replied in the negative. 

</TEXT>

