<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Chernomyrdin Continues U.S. Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prime Minister Chernomyrdin Continues U.S. Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Further Comments on Accords </H4>

<F P=102> LD2406074594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0725 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2406074594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vitaliy Chukseyev] </F>
  [Text] Washington June 24 TASS -- One can say that the 
talks have been a success, Russian Prime Minister Viktor 
Chernomyrdin said on Thursday at the close of the session of 
the Chernomyrin-Gore commission and the Washington part of the 
visit. A total of 26 agreements envisaging the development of 
Russian-U.S. cooperation in various fields have been signed, he 
said. 
  "While in Washington, we signed agremeents, which are in 
point of fact, contracts which will help support our branches of 
industry which have found themselves in a hard position. It is 
primarily a question of space research and space-related 
sectors," Chernomyrdin told ITAR-TASS. 
  "Just as the Sakhalin-2 agreement, they mean the creation of 
a lot of job opportunities and provide a way out in the field of 
financing. Behind these, I perceive the social aspect, i.e. we 
shall not let in agreements which will not provide a solution to 
social issues. Take the agreement on ecology and the power 
industry -- behind them, I see the social welfare aspect as 
well," he said. 
  Touching upon his meeting with U.S. President Bill Clinton 
in the White House on Thursday, Chernomyrdin emphasised that the 
best, most positive evaluation of relations between the two 
countries had been made during the conversation. 
  Asked about an extent to which the forthcoming 
Yeltsin-Clinton meeting in September was discussed during 
Chernomyrdin's stay in Washington, the Russian prime minister 
said the matters were examined but a number of them can be 
decided upon only at the presidential level, not governmental 
one. Besides, it is necessary to see how the agreements signed 
will be implemented and developed, Chernomyrdin said. 

</TEXT>

