<H3> <TI>   Vorontsov Approved as New Ambassador to U.S. </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Vorontsov Approved as New Ambassador to U.S. </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2306145294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1432 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2306145294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] It is now known that members of the parliamentary 
committee for international affairs met in private on Thursday 
to discuss the Yeltsin-proposed list of candidates for 
ambassadorial posts in several countries including the United 
States. 
  The committee approved the president's nominee, Yuliy 
Vorontsov, currently Russian ambassador to the United Nations, 
as head of the Russian embassy in Washington. 
  The post has remained vacant after the previous ambassador 
Vladimir Lukin was elected to parliament and was appointed head 
of its International Affairs Committee. 

