established during the visit to Pyongyang by LDP Deputy Chairman 
Aleksandr Vengerovskiy in April, 1994 on the occasion of Kim 
Il-song's 82d birthday, the same source said. In an interview 
given to ITAR-TASS during the visit Vengerovskiy stressed the 
intention "to maintain an active position as regards North 
Korea." 
  LDP sources said that during Zhirinovskiy's forthcoming 
visit 
an agreement on cooperation will possibly be signed. "We do not 
reject proposals to develop contacts," the same source said. 

