<H3> <TI>   UNESCO Opens Mission in Moscow </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UNESCO Opens Mission in Moscow </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2306112194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1102 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2306112194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vadim Polishchuk] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 23 TASS -- A mission representing the 
United Nations Education, Science and Culture Organisation 
opened its doors for work in the russian capital on Thursday. 
"Our dreams have become a reality," UNESCO Director-General 
Federico Mayor announced at the opening ceremony of the bureau. 
"The opening of this mission became possible as a result of the 
desire and determination of the Russian Government and the 
UNESCO secretariat. It will permit the two sides to cooperate 
more quickly and effectively," he said. 
  "Russia now occupies a most-important place in world 
events," 
Mayor continued. "And our cooperation with it has developed 
wonderfully in the past several years. We have a bunch of joint 
initiatives, among which it would be worthwhile to note those 
projects concerning the Russian state library, the Bolshoy 
theatre, and the Hermitage," the director-general said. 
  "Our organisation's mission is first of all to preserve 
peace," Mayor declared. "Despite the fact that the Cold War is 
a thing of the past, our main goal on the eve of the XXI century 
is to abolish poverty and forever put an end to wars." 

</TEXT>

