<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Denies Aircraft Repairers in Yemen </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman Denies Aircraft Repairers in Yemen </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2306194594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1828 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2306194594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Yuriy Kozlov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 23 TASS -- A report about the alleged 
arrival of a Russian group of specialists from the "Sukhoi" 
aircraft design bureau in the Yemeni capital Sanaa at the 
beginning of June, which appeared in the Saudi Arabian newspaper 
"AL-SHARQ AL-ASWAT", does not conform to reality, Grigoriy 
Karasin, director of the Information and Press Department in the 
Russian Foreign Ministry, said here at a briefing today. 
  Really three officials of the aforesaid design bureau had 
arrived in Sanaa on May 3, that is before armed actions began in 
Yemen, the Russian Foreign Ministry spokesman noted. Their 
visit was aimed at holding talks about the repair of Russian 
made aircraft the Yemeni Army is equipped with. However, not 
getting any opportunity to complete that programme due to 
well-known events, they left for home on May 9, Karasin noted. 
  Regarding the tense situation prevailing in Yemen as a 
result 
of continued armed confrontation, Karasin emphasised, that 
Russia favours an earliest possible end to the fratricide, 
Karasin emphasised. He drew attention towards the necessity of 
unconditionally implementing the U.N. Security Assembly [as 
received] Resolution No. 924, which calls on all sides to 
immediately cease fire and return to the negotiating table to 
resolve differences for the sake of restoring peace and 
stability. According to Karasin, any mediation efforts 
undertaken for the search of a way out of the fratricidal 
conflict in Yemen are supported in Moscow. 

</TEXT>

