<H3> <TI>   Directive on Russian-Tatar Power Delimitation Treaty </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Directive on Russian-Tatar Power Delimitation Treaty </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2206145394 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 21 Jun 94 
p 5 </F>

<F P=103> PM2206145394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Russian Federation President Directive no. 306-rp] </F>
  [Text] With a view to implementing the Russian Federation 
and Republic of Tatarstan treaty "on the delimitation of areas 
of authority and the reciprocal delegation of powers between the 
Russian Federation organs of state power and the Republic of 
Tatarstan organs of state power" and the agreements between the 
Russian Federation Government and the Republic of Tatarstan 
Government and with view to monitoring their observance: 
  1. A commission consisting of representatives of federal 
organs of executive power and Republic of Tatarstan organs of 
executive power shall be created on an equitable basis. 
  2. O.N. Soskovets, first deputy chairman of the Russian 
Federation Government, shall be appointed leader of the 
commission. 
  The commission leader in coordination with the Republic of 
Tatarstan organs of state power shall approve the commission's 
composition. 
  [signed] Russian Federation President B. Yeltsin, 18 June 
1994. 

</TEXT>

