<F P=100> Regional Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tatarstan Representative Appointed to Moscow </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tatarstan Representative Appointed to Moscow </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2406104994 Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI in Russian 24 Jun 94 p 
2 </F>

<F P=103> PM2406104994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Dmitriy Orlov: "Nail Aminov Ready To Cooperate </F>
with All Constructive Politicians"] 
  [Text] In accordance with the treaty between Russia and 
Tatarstan by an edict of President Mintimer Shaymiyev Nail 
Galeyevich Aminov has been appointed Tatarstan's fully empowered 
representative in the Russian Federation. 
  Nail Aminov is a Tatar by nationality. He was born in 1945 
in Kazan and then studied in the Tatar capital. He worked in 
the Bashkir Government. In 1990 he was elected a Russian Soviet 
Federated Socialist Republic people's deputy and worked as a 
committee deputy chairman, subcommittee chairman, and parliament 
department chief. Last year he was appointed deputy chairman of 
a Russian state committee. 
  The Tatarstan representative stated in a talk with your 
ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI correspondent that the main parting message 
given to him by President Shaymiyev was "to serve loyally." In 
Aminov's opinion it is essential that the treaty between Russia 
and Tatarstan should be implemented in all spheres, for which 
the relevant agreements should be concluded. Nail Aminov noted 
that he regards collaboration with the recently created 
Russian-Tatar commission under the leadership of Oleg Soskovets 
as one of the most important tasks facing him and expressed the 
certainty that Vice Premier Sergey Shakhray and minister Nikolay 
Yegorov will take an active part in the commission's work. 
Aminov stated his readiness to cooperate with all Russia's 
political forces "of a constructive bent." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

