<F P=100> Regional Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bashkortostan Premier Praises Accords With Moscow </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bashkortostan Premier Praises Accords With Moscow </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK2306110094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 23 Jun 94 
p 3 </F>

<F P=103> MK2306110094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report under the "NEGA Reports" rubric: </F>
"Bashkortostan"] 
  [Text] Speaking at the current Supreme Soviet session, 
Bashkortostan Prime Minister Anatoliy Koptsev pointed out that 
the recent signing of agreements between the republic and the 
Russian Federation gives Bashkortostan independence in solving 
numerous problems and helps the Russian Government realize the 
need to give broader rights to the regions. In the 
Bashkortostan prime minister's view, the main thing today is to 
devise a mechanism for putting the agreements into practice. 
The 10 agreements that deal mostly with economic matters are 
the result of two years' hard work. The documents cover 
environmental protection, power-sharing with regard to 
state-owned property, customs matters, and international and 
economic relations. From now on the republic will take over 
control of the activity of the fuel and energy sector on its 
territory and will form its currency and gold reserves on its 
own. However, agreements on the budget and relations with the 
Russian Central Bank have yet to be signed. A group of 
officials from the Russian Finance Ministry currently visiting 
Ufa is studying the problem. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

