<F P=100> Regional Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chukchi Region To Trade Oil Products With Europe </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chukchi Region To Trade Oil Products With Europe </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2306170294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1632 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2306170294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Russian government allowed the Chukchi 
Autonomous Area administration to trade in oil products with 
European countries so as to use the hard-currency proceeds for 
purchasing oil products in the Asian-Pacific Region, a source 
close to the government told the Petroleum Information Agency. 
  The government ordinance of June 15 instructs numerous large 
refineries in the Russian West to earmark quotas of oil products 
for the Chukchi peninsula. 
  Experts believe that the decision to allow the Chukchi 
administration to sell oil products to Western Europe and to buy 
them abroad was made because it is cheaper to import fuel to 
Chukchi from abroad than from other regions of Russia. 
  The funds the Russian Finance Ministry raises from 
collecting 
export and import customs duties, levied on export and import of 
oil products earmarked for the Chukchi Autonomous Area, will be 
used to pay for import of these fuels into the area. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-41344 </DOCNO>
