<F P=100> Regional Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Japan To Aid Privatization in Russian Far East </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Japan To Aid Privatization in Russian Far East </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2306122294 Vladivostok Radiostantsiya Tikhiy Okean 
Maritime Network in Russian 0715 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2306122294 </F>
<F P=104>  Vladivostok Radiostantsiya Tikhiy Okean 
Maritime Network </F>

<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Pacific Ocean" Program] </F>
  [Text] A regional privatization voucher outlet opened in 
Maritime Kray center. Its main goal is extending post 
privatization assistance to Russian companies in Siberia and the 
Far East. It is largely a commercial structure, and was founded 
by the European Bank of Reconstruction and Development and the 
Japanese Foreign Ministry. Its capital of $30 million will be 
used to finance the vitality of investment projects. Moreover, 
the Japanese Government will extend assistance to the Fund for 
Technical Aid to the tune of $20 million. Speaking at opening 
of the new investment structure, Nobuachi Ito, representative of 
the Japanese Foreign Ministry, announced that the Land of the 
Rising Sun had high hopes for cooperation with enterprises of 
this region of Russia because the privatization program has been 
implemented here with the greatest degree of success. The 
Japanese expect a positive response from local industrialists, 
and hope for long-term and fruitful cooperation. 

</TEXT>

