<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chairmanship of Black Sea Assembly To Be Assumed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chairmanship of Black Sea Assembly To Be Assumed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2406091694 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 1400 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2406091694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Our correspondent has met at Boryspil airport with 
a Ukrainian parliamentary delegation headed by Oleksandr 
Tkachenko, first deputy chairman of the Supreme Council. The 
Ukrainian parliamentarians returned today after participating in 
a session of the Black Sea Parliamentary Assembly in Bucharest. 
Among those who met the delegation at the airport was Romanian 
Ambassador to Ukraine Ion Bistreanu. Now, let us listen to an 
interview with Oleksandr Mykolayovych Tkachenko, conducted 
immediately after the delegation's arrival. 
  [Begin Tkachenko recording] The assembly of nine European 
and Asian states aims at uniting their efforts after the Council 
for Mutual Economic Assistance ceased to exist. We believe that 
Ukraine has made a correct step by joining the Black Sea 
Assembly. The topics discussed at this session, and it was 
already the third one, primarily concerned economic issues, as 
well as the role and place of Ukraine among other states [words 
indistinct]. The third topic discussed concerned cultural and 
social ties among our states. In addition to these nine states, 
Bulgaria and Greece were invited to participate in the Black 
Sea Assembly session as observers, and we believe that they will 
join this organization in the near future. 
  We believe that the Ukrainian delegation accomplished its 
mission, because we defended our position, which envisions that 
the next assembly session will be chaired by Supreme Council 
Chairman Oleksandr Moroz. [Words indistinct] Ukraine will be 
chairing the assembly during this period. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

