<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Moroz on Black Sea Fleet, Relations With CIS </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moroz on Black Sea Fleet, Relations With CIS </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2306171094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1628 
GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2306171094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by UKRINFORM correspondent Viktor Kovalenko for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Kiev, 23 Jun -- Ukrainian Supreme Council Chairman 
Aleksandr Moroz has said that he sees a solution to the problem 
of the Black Sea Fleet in an arrangement whereby Russia and 
Ukraine will execute joint command of the fleet but each side 
would be responsible for the financial and organizational 
aspects of running its share of the fleet. He said so at a news 
conference today. 
  The Supreme Council head said that Ukraine's agreements with 
the CIS countries ought to be deepened because they are not 
working at the moment and no one is trying to make them work. 
He said he was concerned with the fact that the world community 
was attempting to turn Ukraine into an appendage supplying raw 
resources, and spoke in favor of setting up and developing 
self-contained production cycles in the state, which would meet 
Ukraine's demand for the main types of industrial products. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

