Daily Report 
<DATE1>  22 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Naval Forces Press Center Disputes Black Sea Fleet Press </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Naval Forces Press Center Disputes Black Sea Fleet Press </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2206185794 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1530 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2206185794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] [No dateline as received] -- On 22 June the 
Ukrainian Naval Forces' press center announced that some of the 
mass media circulated reports by the Black Sea Fleet press 
center to the effect that "addressing the electorate of the city 
of Donetsk, Ukraine's Supreme Council Speaker Oleksandr Moroz 
spoke out for a single Black Sea Fleet, which should serve the 
interests of the fraternal peoples of Ukraine and Russia." It 
was also reported that Oleksandr Moroz believed the Black Sea 
Fleet should be commanded jointly, following NATO's example. 
  The Ukrainian Naval Forces' press center declares that the 
Black Sea Fleet press center's report grossly distorts the 
meaning of the statement made by Ukraine's Supreme Council 
chairman concerning the solution of the Black Sea Fleet issue. 
In Donetsk Oleksandr Moroz spoke out in favor of setting up a 
united command of the Ukrainian and Russian fleets on the Black 
Sea. At the same time he emphasized that "this command should 
be united, not a joint one." 
  The Ukrainian Naval Forces command believes that the 
leadership of the Black Sea Fleet thus, mistakes the wish for 
the reality and reiterates that the negotiating process on the 
Black Sea Fleet division is continuing at the governmental level 
at which both sides point out unequivocally that the fleet must 
be divided. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

