<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   No Winners in Presidential Elections; 2d Round in Jul </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    No Winners in Presidential Elections; 2d Round in Jul </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2406050194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0337 
GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2406050194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From BELINFORM by a TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Minsk, 24 June -- It has not been possible to 
reveal who will be the first president of the Republic of 
Belarus: Such are the preliminary results of the first round of 
the elections which took place on Thursday [23 June]. 
  And even though the final data will be received later it can 
already be said now that Aleksandr Lukashenko who collected 
44-45 percent of the vote is more than twice ahead of his main 
competitor Vyacheslav Kebich (18-19 per cent). The other 
candidates rank in the following order: Zenon Poznyak, Stanislav 
Shushkevich, Aleksandr Dubo, and Vasiliy Novikov, with the 
leader of the Belarusian People's Front Zenon Poznyak having 
approximately five percent less votes than V.Kebich. 
  Chairman of the Central Electoral Commission Aleksandr 
Abramovich said that for the time being three dates for the 
second round are being discussed: 7, 10, or 17 July 1994. In 
accordance with the legislation, Aleksandr Lukashenko and 
Vyacheslav Kebich will be permitted to take part in this round. 

</TEXT>

