<H3> <TI>   73 Percent of Voters Cast Ballots </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    73 Percent of Voters Cast Ballots </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2306200994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1914 
GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2306200994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by BELINFORM correspondent--TASS] </F>
  [Text] Minsk, 23 June -- A BELINFORM correspondent was told 
by the Central Electoral Commission that as of 1900, 73 percent 
of the voters had participated in the elections for the 
country's first president. The highest turnout in the secret 
ballot was among the residents of Brest Oblast, with 78.7 
percent having cast their votes. In some rayons of the oblast 
the turnout reached 86-87 percent of the total electorate. The 
lowest turnout was in the capital, where only 64.4 percent of 
the electorate had voted by 1900 local time. Some 356 polling 
stations finished their work ahead of the deadline. 

</TEXT>

