<F P=106> [Report by Ivan Hladkin from the Central Electoral </F>
Commission] 
  [Excerpt] [Passage omitted] I want to make all our 
listeners happy by telling them that according to preliminary 
calculations just provided by the Central Electoral Commission, 
the presidential elections in Belarus have taken place. In 
Belarus in general, 63.6 percent of electors cast their votes by 
1200 GMT. Turnover was highest in Brest Oblast -- 70.3 percent; 
in Vitebsk Oblast -- 64.4 percent; in Gomel Oblast -- 65.4 
percent; in Grodno Oblast -- 63.8 percent; in Mogilev Oblast -- 
64.4. percent; in Minsk Oblast -- 65 percent; in the city of 
Minsk -- 53 percent. In the Republic in general, elections have 
been completed at 240 polling stations. [passage omitted] 

