BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed NEGA report in the "Uzbekistan" column] </F>
  [Text] Informed sources say that Uzbek President Islam 
Karimov recently had a kidney removal operation. In this 
connection all scheduled meetings with various delegation were 
cancelled. True, he was present at a cabinet of ministers 
session devoted to the introduction of the national currency. 
According to eyewitness accounts, he did not look very well and 
was present for only 20 minutes. His visit to Turkey, scheduled 
for 23 June, has not been canceled, though. In the course of 
the visit a number of earlier signed agreements bearing on 
credits, investments, student and teacher exchanges, and so 
forth, are expected to be revised. 

</TEXT>

