<F P=100> Uzbekistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Turkish Talks End With Signing of 4 Documents </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Turkish Talks End With Signing of 4 Documents </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2406082294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0729 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2406082294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Sergey Feoktistov] </F>
  [Text] Ankara 24 June TASS -- Uzbek-Turkish official talks 
ended here on Thursday [23 June] by the signing of four 
bilateral documents. The delegations were headed by President 
Islam Karimov of Uzbekistan, who arrived in Turkey on Thursday, 
and president Suleyman Demirel of Turkey. The sides concluded 
agreements on mutual assistance in the science of law, 
development of contacts in civil aviation, a consular agreement 
and a protocol on cosultations and cooperation between the 
foreign ministries of the two countries. 
  The signed documents, a statement of the Turkish Foreign 
Ministry notes, will contribute to the solution of issues in 
actively devoloping relations between Turkey and Uzbekistan. 
Bilateral contacts are quickly developing in the sphere of 
trade, economy and culture. 
  During the talks the sides expressed a mutual desire to 
begin 
works as soon as possible for signing an agreement regarding the 
cancellation of vizas for citizens of the two republics. Both 
sides spoke out in favour of invigorating relations in the 
political field by means of mutual consultations and actions on 
the international arena. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

