<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Views Transportation Cooperation With Romania </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Views Transportation Cooperation With Romania </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2406081094 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 2040 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2406081094 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chisinau, ROMPRES, 22/06/1994 -- Tomorrow, a 
delegation of the Moldovan Ministry of Transportation headed by 
Minister Vasili Iovv, will leave for Bucharest to meet with 
representatives of the Romanian Transportation Ministry. Vasile 
Iovv told BASA that "the visit's purpose is to establish 
cooperation relations in the field of transportation that will 
yield profits to both states." Nicolae Ciobanu, deputy head of 
the Roads Department, told BASA that negotiations on building a 
bridge across the Prut at Radauti-Lipcani will be also 
discussed. According to Ciobanu, a program on developing and 
integrating Moldovan highway networks into the European system 
will be elaborated. A program on repairing the bridges across 
the Prut at Galati-Giurgiulesti, Oancea-Cahul and 
Stanca-Costenti and the highways at these border points will be 
drafted. According to the Galati agreement, these highways will 
be passed to international regulations. Ciobanu pointed out 
that a joint administration of the navigation on the Prut river 
with an autonomous regulation of organization and functioning 
will be created. Vasile Iovv stated to BASA that the railway 
gauge will not be yet passed to the Romanian standards as 
Moldova does not have sufficient funding for such works. The 
last meeting between Moldovan and Romanian Transportation 
Ministries occurred in November 1993. 

</TEXT>

