<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Snegur Seeks Parliamentary Approval of Economic Plan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Snegur Seeks Parliamentary Approval of Economic Plan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2306170594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1633 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2306170594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Mircea Snegur has called for parliamentary 
approval of the government-proposed economic recovery plan for 
1994-97. 
  He said that as a first stage, it was important to curb 
inflation so as to strengthen the entire infrastructure of the 
market economy. 
  "If we fail to do this quickly, there will be a new round of 
inflation leading to most dire implications," Snegur said. 
  The president spoke against emergency economic measures 
calling instead for calm and regaining public trust. 
  At the same time, he admitted that initial conditions for 
implementing the government program were bad: there was a 
further slump in production, widespread stoppages and very low 
investment activity. 
  Snegur named budgetary, financial and crediting policies, 
industrial reorganization, privatization, utilization of the 
workforce and social security safeguards as key problems facing 
the government. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

