<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official Claims Many Enterprises Controlled by Mafia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official Claims Many Enterprises Controlled by Mafia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2406133294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1053 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2406133294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Isa Kostoyev, Chairman of the Federation Council 
Committee on constitutional legislature and legal issues, 
declared to Interfax Friday that there is official statistical 
data in the Interior Ministry and Federal Counterintelligence 
Service stating that many Russian state enterprises are under 
the control of mafia structures. 
  "There are thousands of criminal trials carried out due to 
this fact. For example, the products of industrial enterprises 
in many regions is quite competitive with imported goods brought 
by commercial structures and criminal elements urge that these 
enterprises export their production outside the region. A 
director is forced to obey because he does not want to subject 
his own life and his family to danger." 
  "Not to speak about those commercial enterprises which 
cannot 
make a single move without the knowledge of the mafia," Kostoyev 
added. "I know that in the Western world the mafia also exerts 
certain pressure, but it does not touch upon state enterprises. 
We have already left the West far behind in this sphere, he 
pointed out. Given the current situation it is necessary to use 
emergency measures to combat organized crime but it should be 
done in the frameworks of precise laws so that innocent people 
do not suffer," Kostoyev said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

