Daily Report 
<DATE1>  23 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Soskovets Raps Fuel Ministry Forecasts </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Soskovets Raps Fuel Ministry Forecasts </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2306140394 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1300 GMT 
23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2306140394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At today's meeting of the cabinet, Oleg Soskovets, 
Russian first deputy prime minister, voiced his dissatisfaction 
with the Ministry of Fuel and Power Engineering's position while 
discussing the issue of how enterprises and organizations were 
preparing for the fall and winter period. According to him, the 
panic-stricken pronouncements by the ministry's representative 
to the effect that we will not survive this winter can mean only 
one thing: Such people should be found who will be able to 
organize work in a new way. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>
